<scopecontent><head>Scope and Contents note</head><p>	In 1910, Marion's mother Frances Cooke Holden, died, Letters concerning Marion's guardianship, her first communication with her estranged father, and letters from her young half-brothers and sisters make up an early part of this series. Letters from her step-mother, Marie Sprague Holden, are especially endearing. Also of note in this series is a letter and autographed photograph of actor and author Otis Skinner (Box 1:2) and a series of letters to and from T.V. Smith, Illinois State Senator and philosopher (Box 3:5 and 3:6),						</p></scopecontent>					
