<c01 level="series"><did><unittitle>	Series II: Personal and Professional Life						</unittitle></did>					
<scopecontent><head>Scope and Contents note</head><p>	The oldest items in the collection appear in this series as letters to Frances Cooke Holden, dating from 1891.											
	Marion Holden Bemis, like her paternal grandfather, was a prolific writer. This series also includes her many articles, published and unpublished, along with sketches, paintings and personal papers. She was actively involved in a number of organizations, particularly with Detroit's Women's City Club, where she served as editor of the club magazine for eighteen years.						</p></scopecontent>					
